{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_42","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `io.opentelemetry.semconv:opentelemetry-semconv:1.24.0-alpha`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-5651-fails-javac-compile-io.opentelemetry.semconv-opentelemetry-semconv-1.24.0-alpha-632c5173\n\nThe most likely failing stage was the automated `javac` test-rewrite step. In `human-intervention-logs/io.opentelemetry.semconv:opentelemetry-semconv:1.24.0-alpha/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T07-41-42-243433Z.log`, `compileTestJava` fails because `Opentelemetry_semconvTest.java` still imports `io.opentelemetry.semconv.ResourceAttributes` and `io.opentelemetry.semconv.SemanticAttributes`, and the compiler reports `cannot find symbol` for those classes and many of their constants. The fixer log at `human-intervention-logs/io.opentelemetry.semconv:opentelemetry-semconv:1.24.0-alpha/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-04T07-43-44-695870Z.log` shows the intended migration path: `1.24.0-alpha` uses split classes such as `HttpAttributes`, `NetworkAttributes`, `UrlAttributes`, `ServerAttributes`, `ClientAttributes`, `ErrorAttributes`, `JvmAttributes`, `UserAgentAttributes`, and `SchemaUrls` instead of the old monolithic API.\n\nThere are later passing reruns in `human-intervention-logs/io.opentelemetry.semconv:opentelemetry-semconv:1.24.0-alpha/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T07-43-44-737223Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/io.opentelemetry.semconv:opentelemetry-semconv:1.24.0-alpha/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T07-46-34-921539Z.log`, but the automation did not preserve a usable fix artifact. `stats/io.opentelemetry.semconv/opentelemetry-semconv/1.24.0-alpha/execution-metrics.json` still reports `status: failure`, `iterations: 1`, `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, and `metadata_file: None`, so there is no committed patch to reuse directly.\n\nManual next steps:\n1. Recreate the `1.24.0-alpha` test update by replacing `SemanticAttributes`/`ResourceAttributes` usages with the split `io.opentelemetry.semconv` classes referenced in the fixer log.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.opentelemetry.semconv:opentelemetry-semconv:1.24.0-alpha` from a clean checkout to confirm both `compileTestJava` and `nativeTest`.\n3. Commit the recreated test fix on a normal branch if it passes, since the preserved branch contains logs/metrics context but not a reusable fix commit."}}
